{
  "doc_id": "39163",
  "text": "It has been indicated that HDAC inhibitors can reverse the abnormal histone acetylation and improve memory, thus reversing the disease process. When APP/PS1 mice are exposed to a frightening environment, the level of H4 acetylation in the hippocampus is lower than in wild-type mice. After receiving trichostatin A, the acetylation level of H4 increases and the stiffness in the dreaded environment becomes more obvious [CITATION_1] . If transgenic CK-p25 mice were given trichostatin, the dendrites and synapses were induced to proliferate and the learning and memory ability could be recovered as well [CITATION_2] . Valproate, an inhibitor of HDAC, could effectively improve the episodic memory of ADAPPswe/PS1dE9 transgenic mice [CITATION_3] . Another inhibitor of HDAC, such as phenyl butyrate, could reverse the spatial memory loss and the level of phosphated tau protein in the hippocampus in Tg2576 mice. However, it could not change the level of Aβ [CITATION_4] .",
